attempts.sparql_query:
PREFIX atm: <http://www.atm.org/ontology#> 
PREFIX nas: <http://www.nas.org/ontology#> 
SELECT ?flight ?passengers 
WHERE { ?flight a atm:Flight ; nas:passengerCapacity ?passengers . FILTER (?passengers > 100) }
attempts.query_explanation: This SPARQL query selects flights that have a passenger capacity greater than 100. It uses the `nas:passengerCapacity` property to retrieve the number of passengers each flight can carry.
